@Ravindra How? 

My baby ?: is what we call the Elvis operator, he takes care of falsy values: zero, empty string, null etc.

It is exactly the same as writing in the regular ternary form:
$imagePath = ($this->image) ? $this->image : 'noimage.jpg';

Or in the if else form:
if ($this->image) {
    $imagePath = $this->image;
} else {
    $imagePath = 'noimage.jpg';
}

The elvis is better because it is easier to read and works for falsy values.
The null coalescing operator only works for *null* values. So if, say, $this->image is false somehow, it will not peform the intended functionality because false !== null.

