I just ran in the same issue, if you are still having that problem:
Check if you are using strict equality in the update method in ProfilePolicy,
    public function update(User $user, Profile $profile)
    {
      return $user->id === $profile->user_id;
    }
If you dd both values, you will realize that $user->id is a number, while $profile->user_id is a string, therefore this comparison will always return false and you will never be able to reach the view.


Either use == or convert the user_id to a number:
    public function update(User $user, Profile $profile)
    {
      return $user->id === intval($profile->user_id);
    }

